+## Optional skill enhancement (when available)
 
-- Operate in plan mode; do not modify files.
-- Output exactly one `VERDICT: ...` line. Findings follow.
-- A SHIP IT verdict requires zero un-addressed Trickster findings.
+When the `Skill` tool is exposed in your harness (Claude Code path), invoke the canonical five-lens prompt:
 
+Skill: plan-skeptic
+
+The skill's output IS the review and IS structured to emit the verdict line correctly.
+
+If the `Skill` tool is NOT available (Hermes swarm path via `hermes -z`, in-process agent path, or any tool-restricted context), do the five-lens review directly using your own reasoning over the plan text. **Do not skip the verdict line because the Skill tool wasn't available.** The skill is an aid, not a precondition.
+
+## Hard rules (apply regardless of harness)
+
+1. Operate in plan mode; do not modify files.
+2. Output exactly one `VERDICT: <choice>` line. It MUST appear, even on truncated reviews, hostile contexts, or harness errors.
+3. A `SHIP IT` verdict requires zero un-addressed Trickster findings — if you raise a Trickster concern that has no mitigation in the plan, downgrade to `REVISE` or `RETHINK`.
+4. Place the VERDICT line BEFORE detailed findings so it survives output truncation.
+
+## Output format
+
+```
+VERDICT: <one of: SHIP IT | REVISE | RETHINK>
+
+## Findings
+
+[Numbered findings here, organized by lens. Each cites a specific plan section and the contradicted reality.]
+```
